KW  - Internet
KW  - Social media
KW  - Transnational terrorism
AB  - Does the internet enable the recruitment of transnational terrorists? Using geo-referenced population census data and personnel records from the Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant – a highly tech-savvy terrorist organization – this paper shows that internet access has facilitated the organization’s recruitment of foreign fighters from Tunisia. The positive association between internet access and Daesh recruitment is concentrated among younger cohorts.
